cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.DM, cs.MS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm based on a simple Interval Tree data structure for computing intersections among d-rectangles. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on taking advantage of the multiprocessing capabilities of modern multicore processors to improve the performance of the algorithm. 
3. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm and compares it with two widely used solutions. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with the problem of identifying intersections among a set of d-dimensional rectangular regions, which can be considered a problem in discrete mathematics. 
5. cs.MS (Mathematical Software) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for a common problem in simulation and modeling applications, which can be considered a contribution to mathematical software.
